====================================================================
  L6 INTERVIEW TIPS FOR TREE QUESTIONS
====================================================================

1. CLARIFY FIRST:
   - Binary tree or BST?
   - Can values repeat?
   - Can nodes be null / tree be empty?
   - Are parent pointers available?
   - Is it a balanced tree? (affects complexity guarantees)

2. RECURSION PATTERNS TO MASTER:
   - Bottom-up (post-order return values)     -> height, diameter, LCA
   - Top-down (pass state down)               -> path sum, validate BST
   - Global variable + local return           -> max path sum (LC 124)
   - Two-pointer / Two-tree recursion         -> same tree, symmetric

3. ITERATIVE ALTERNATIVES (L6 bar):
   - Know iterative inorder (stack)
   - Know Morris traversal (O(1) space) for L6 differentiation
   - Know BFS with (node, level) or (node, col)

4. EDGE CASES:
   - Empty tree (root == None)
   - Single node
   - Skewed tree (all left or all right -> O(N) depth)
   - Duplicate values
   - Negative values (matters for LC 124)

5. COMPLEXITY:
   - Most tree problems: O(N) time, O(H) space (H = height)
   - Balanced: H = log N; Skewed: H = N
   - BFS: O(N) time, O(W) space (W = max width)


